<Window x:Class="OverWatchELD.Views.ReadMeWindow"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        Title="OverWatch ELD - Read-me" Height="640" Width="880"
        WindowStartupLocation="CenterOwner"
        Background="#101114"
        Foreground="White">
    <Grid Margin="18">
        <Grid.RowDefinitions>
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
            <RowDefinition Height="*"/>
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
        </Grid.RowDefinitions>

        <TextBlock FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Text="Read-me / How to Use" />

        <ScrollViewer Grid.Row="1" Margin="0,12,0,12" VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
            <StackPanel>
                <TextBlock FontSize="14" TextWrapping="Wrap">
OverWatch ELD is a driver-focused ELD-style companion for ATS with duty status, logs, DVIR, messaging, and VTC/Discord integration.
                </TextBlock>

                <Separator Margin="0,12,0,12"/>

                <TextBlock FontSize="16" FontWeight="SemiBold" Text="Quick Start" />
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0" FontSize="14" TextWrapping="Wrap">
1) Launch OverWatch ELD and log in.
2) Verify the dashboard clocks and duty buttons.
3) Configure Companion / Telemetry if you want auto-duty and location.
4) (Optional) Enable Discord Bot integration in Settings for Dispatch + Announcements.
                </TextBlock>

                <Separator Margin="0,12,0,12"/>

                <TextBlock FontSize="16" FontWeight="SemiBold" Text="Discord / VTC" />
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0" FontSize="14" TextWrapping="Wrap">
• Dispatch messages: Dispatch channel → ELD inbox. ELD replies go back to the dispatch channel.
• Linking: In ELD, generate a one-time code, then DM the bot: !link ABC123.
• VTC roster: The VTC page can show roster pulled from the bot (https://overwatcheld-bot.up.railway.app/api/vtc/roster).
                </TextBlock>

                <Separator Margin="0,12,0,12"/>

                <TextBlock FontSize="16" FontWeight="SemiBold" Text="BOL (Bill of Lading)" />
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0" FontSize="14" TextWrapping="Wrap">
Use BOL to capture load details (pickup/delivery, notes). Export sends a file attachment to your Discord webhook (if configured).
                </TextBlock>

                <Separator Margin="0,12,0,12"/>

                <TextBlock FontSize="16" FontWeight="SemiBold" Text="Tips" />
                <TextBlock Margin="0,6,0,0" FontSize="14" TextWrapping="Wrap">
• If the Discord bot HTTP API says “conflicts with an existing registration”, change BotApiPort in vtc.config.json.
• If roster doesn’t load, start the bot first, then refresh the VTC roster page.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>
        </ScrollViewer>

        <Button Grid.Row="2" Content="Close" Width="120" HorizontalAlignment="Right" Click="Close_Click"/>
    </Grid>
</Window>
